Package org.apache.hadoop.fs.swift.exceptions

Exception Summary
SwiftAuthenticationFailedException An exception raised when an authentication request was rejected
SwiftBadRequestException Thrown to indicate that data locality can't be calculated or requested path is incorrect.
SwiftConfigurationException Exception raised to indicate there is some problem with how the Swift FS is configured
SwiftConnectionClosedException Exception raised when an attempt is made to use a closed stream
SwiftConnectionException Thrown to indicate that connection is lost or failed to be made
SwiftException A Swift-specific exception -subclasses exist for various specific problems.
SwiftInternalStateException The internal state of the Swift client is wrong -presumably a sign of some bug
SwiftInvalidResponseException Exception raised when the HTTP code is invalid.
SwiftJsonMarshallingException Exception raised when the J/O mapping fails.
SwiftNotDirectoryException Exception raised when an operation is meant to work on a directory, but the target path is not a directory
SwiftOperationFailedException Used to relay exceptions upstream from the inner implementation to the public API, where it is downgraded to a log+failure.
SwiftPathExistsException Exception raised when trying to create a file that already exists and the overwrite flag is set to false.
SwiftThrottledRequestException Exception raised if a Swift endpoint returned a HTTP response indicating the caller is being throttled.
SwiftUnsupportedFeatureException Exception raised on an unsupported feature in the FS API -such as append()
